This paper investigates the composition of search engine results pages, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The study also involves analyzing the content of the results pages, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques to improve search results, which could be relevant to deep learning (cs.DL).
